               <head/>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85100085">
                  <summary>Mas̱navī-i Maʿnavī, Book 5 of 6</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_39-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="305v"/>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20506">Mas̱navī-i Maʿnavī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20506">مثنوی معنوی</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176928.0x000001 viaf_98930150">Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_98930150">جلال الدین رومی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">شه حسام الدین که نور انجم است *** طالب آغاز سفر پنجم است </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">همین بجو تریاق فاروق ایغلام *** تا شوی فاروق دوران والسلام</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>Jones commissioned the six volumes of the Mas̱navī which make up MSs RSPA 35-40. This is clear from a note in MS RSPA 35 in which he acknowledges the scribe: "Written by Maulavī Aâzzu'ddīn began 21 Jan 1790. Began 21 Jan. 1790 25S.R. a month, asked; 30S.R. given". The scribe's name was <persName key="person_f8182" role="scr">Mavlavī ʿIzz al-Dīn</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Before the textblock, Jones writes, "Indorum / μυδηγιον - Illo sole prostantius lumen  dei meditemur mentes qui nostrum dirigat! / allias; illud sole &amp;c / alias; illud solis prostantissimum lumen divi meditemur &amp;c / alias; illud summi numinis optimum lumein dei meditemur et caetera sic trivedi servoru" in which he describes (supposed) sun-worship among the Indians. </p>
                     </note>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">تمام شد دفتر خامس مثنوی مولوی جلال الدین رومی</colophon>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
